# File Organization Rules

**NEVER create markdown documentation files in the project root.** Only `README.md` is allowed at root.

## Locations

| Content Type               | Location            |
| -------------------------- | ------------------- |
| Implementation, testing, migrations, ADRs | `docs/development/` |
| Security, auth, encryption | `docs/security/`   |
| Requirements, user guides | `docs/product/`    |

## Conventions

- **kebab-case** filenames; descriptive (e.g. `multi-tenant-implementation.md`).
- When creating docs: pick the correct `docs/` subdir, create there, update section README if needed.

See `docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md` and `docs/README.md` for full standards.
